title: Grateful Dead Live at Orpheum Theatre on 1976-07-14
lineage: Cassette (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6MHz) > Sound Forge Pro 13 (WAV 24-bit/96k) > DDi Codec (Dolby B) > Samplitude Pro X5 Suite (24-bit/48k) > FLAC/24
taper: Thanks to Dennis Koda for the cassettes
description:
Set I
Promised Land
Sugaree
New Minglewood Blues
Scarlet Begonias
Looks Like Rain
They Love Each Other
Mama Tried
Ship Of Fools
Playing In The Band >
Drums >
The Wheel >
Playing In The Band
Set II
Brown Eyed Women >
Samson & Delilah
Friend Of The Devil
Let It Grow >
Eyes Of The World >
Wharf Rat >
The Other One >
The Music Never Stopped

Encore:
Johnny B. Goode


Comment
Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Keith Godchaux - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums
Donna Jean Godchaux - Vocals

reviews.review_text: Fantastic This Charlie Miller transfer sounds great, and the SF Orpheum run is one of my faves, along with the June 76 box and the Tower Theatre shows.June July 76 was money.
